content: The ASPCA was founded in 1866 and was the first animal welfare organization in North America. Our mission is to provide effective means for the prevention of cruelty to animals throughout the United States.

We provide animal rescue and placement, animal health services, anti-cruelty initiatives, and community outreach programs. Our work includes disaster response, animal behavior training, and legislative advocacy.
